    "created_at": "2015-02-12T11:25:00Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-02-12T11:25:00Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "What is the rationale behind the removing of `{` and `}` tokens at if/else/for statements with a single following statement?\n\nCode like this becomes hard to read: https://github.com/ScottNZ/OpenRA/blob/stylecop-fixes/OpenRA.Mods.Common/UtilityCommands/UpgradeRules.cs#L225-LL227\n\nAnd it's also a cause of bugs: http://embeddedgurus.com/barr-code/2014/03/apples-gotofail-ssl-security-bug-was-easily-preventable/\n\nI'm not a C# coder, so if this is just the accepted C# style then never mind. I don't want to start a huge styling debate here..\n"
  },
